Okay, wow… you weren't kidding when you said wordy, were you?

Okay, three things.

One, paragraphs. Seriously, blocks of text are inordinately hard on the eyes, and decrease interest in reading something. Try and sort that out.

Two, formatting. It always looks better when you bold titles, put speech sections in quote boxes, and put little quotes in italics. It makes them stand out, and again, easier to read.

Three, if you've got support documents that long, you might want to put them into a separate document here, simply for simplification and the sake of clarity.

Other than that, the idea seems sound. It's just your formatting skills need work, and maybe being a little more impartial in your writing.





